15/01/2008
NEW YORK, United States -- UN spokesperson Michele Montas said on Monday (January 14th) that talks between Greece and Macedonia on remaining issues, including their long-standing name dispute, will continue next week. 
Talks are to resume on January 21st in Ohrid, Macedonia, the first time they are being held outside of UN headquarters in New York. 
They will be held under the auspices of UN special envoy Matthew Nimetz. 
(Makfax - 15/01/08; UN web site, Voice of America - 14/01/08)
